 To ensure that the posterior belongs to the same distribution family as
 the prior distribution, we choose Inverse-Wishart distribution which is
 in a Bayesian statistic a common choice as a conjugate prior for the covariance
 matrix of a multivariate normal distribution with known mean
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Kendall2004"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 That is the case for 
\begin_inset Formula $\mat P_{k|k-1}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mat R_{k}$
\end_inset

, which are both the covariances matrices of Gaussian PDFs as is in equations
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:predxkprob"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
