\Xi(\Psi,\nu,p)= & \Bigl[\begin{array}{cc}
-\frac{1}{2}\boldsymbol{\Psi} & -\dfrac{\nu+p+1}{2}\end{array}\Bigr]\\
A(\eta)= & \frac{\nu}{2}(p\ln2-\ln|\boldsymbol{\Psi}|)-\ln\Gamma_{p}\left(\frac{\nu}{2}\right)
\end{align*}

\end_inset

The first element 
